org.lsmr.vending.frontend2

Interface IVendingMachineFactory


  • public interface IVendingMachineFactory
    This interface specifies a set of event callbacks that your vending machine implementation has to implement. The frontend calls these callbacks when the corresponding script commands are encountered. The factory maintains a set of vending machines, indexed from 0 to (number of vending machines - 1).

    • Method Detail

      • configureVendingMachine

        void configureVendingMachine(int vmIndex,
                             java.util.List<java.lang.String> popNames,
                             java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> popCosts)
        Configures the indicated vending machine to use the indicated names and costs for the pop kinds related to the selection buttons at the indexed position. For example, the string at position 0 of popNames is to be used as the name of the pops loaded into the vending machine that would be vended by selection button 0. PopCan names and pop costs DO NOT need to be unique.
        Parameters:
        vmIndex - The index of the vending machine to configure.
        popNames - A list of the names to use for the pop cans. The length must equal the number of selection buttons in the machine. Each index position in the list corresponds to the selection button with the same index. Names must be legal names. The same name can be used for more than one position. Names can be enclosed in double-quotation marks (like "this") in which case these marks are stripped off.
        popCosts - A list of the costs to use for the pop cans. The length must equal the number of selection buttons in the machine. Each index position in the list corresponds to the selection button with the same index. Costs must be greater than 0. The same cost can be used for more than one position.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the index is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the number of vending machines currently constructed.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If any arguments are null, if the number of elements in either list is not identical to the number of selection buttons for the vending machine, if a pop name is not a string at least 1 character long, or if a pop cost is not a positive integer.

      • constructNewVendingMachine

        int constructNewVendingMachine(java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> coinKinds,
                               int selectionButtonCount,
                               int coinRackCapacity,
                               int popCanRackCapacity,
                               int receptacleCapacity)
        Constructs a vending machine that accepts a specified set of coin kinds (positive integer denominations) and a certain number of pop selection buttons. Coin kinds must have unique denominations. The constructed vending machine is indexed with the next available number (i.e., the first vending machine has index 0, the second has index 1, etc.). The system starts WITHOUT any vending machine constructed by default.
        Parameters:
        coinKinds - A list of the values to be used for valid coin kinds. The values must be unique. The values must be positive. Any order can be used, but the order will be used for later reference.
        selectionButtonCount - The number of selection buttons that the vending machine should have. Must be greater than 0.
        receptacleCapacity - The maximum number of items that can be stored in each receptacle and delivery chute.
        popCanRackCapacity - The maximum number of items that can be stored in each pop can rack.
        coinRackCapacity - The maximum number of items that can be stored in each coin rack.
        Returns:
        The index of the vending machine just constructed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any of the coin kinds is not positive or if the selection button count is not positive
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the coin kinds do not have unique denominations

      • extractFromDeliveryChute

        java.util.List<Deliverable> extractFromDeliveryChute(int vmIndex)
        Called to remove all coins and pop cans from the delivery chute of the vending machine, returning them in whatever order is convenient (as Coin and PopCan instances). Should not prevent the vending machine from continuing to function.
        Parameters:
        vmIndex - The index of the vending machine to use.
        Returns:
        A list of removed coins and pop cans from the delivery chute, as described above.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the vmIndex is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the number of vending machines currently constructed.

      • insertCoin

        void insertCoin(int vmIndex,
                Coin coin)
         throws DisabledException
        Called to insert a coin in a vending machine.
        Parameters:
        vmIndex - The index of the vending machine used.
        coin - The coin inserted in the machine. Cannot be null.
        Throws:
        DisabledException - If the hardware is disabled.
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the vmIndex is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the number of vending machines currently constructed.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If the coin argument is null.

      • loadCoins

        void loadCoins(int vmIndex,
               int coinKindIndex,
               Coin... coins)
        A set of coins is ADDED to the indicated vending machine. Note that it is legal to load coins of the wrong kind into the location intended for another coin kind; this will lead to incorrect coins being returned at times, but the vending machine will otherwise function normally.
        Parameters:
        vmIndex - The index of the vending machine to use.
        coinKindIndex - The index of the coin kinds in which to add the coins.
        coins - A sequence of the coins to add to the machine.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If the vmIndex is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the number of vending machines currently constructed; or if the coinKindIndex is less than 0 or greater than or equal to the number of coin kinds in the indicated vending machine.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If any of the arguments is null

      • loadPopCans

        void loadPopCans(int vmIndex,
                 int popCanRackIndex,
                 PopCan... popCans)
        Loads a list of pop cans into the pop can rack at the indicated index.
        Parameters:
        vmIndex - The index of the vending machine used.
        popCanRackIndex - The index of the pop can rack to be used.
        popCans - A sequence of pop cans to be loaded. Cannot be null. Can be empty.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - If the list is null.
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - If either index is < 0 or >= number of pop can racks.
